comments.body:
@zvonkok I know that CDI support was recently merged in #10081. Would there be benefit in driving this further? From the NVIDIA side, we could provide tooling to generate a CDI spec for the available devices. This could then be consumed by podman and other container runtimes as these start to offer CDI support.

Other vendors or users could then define the specs for their devices.

cc @bart0sh

@rhatdan Several folks from different companies are working on this: [https://github.com/container-orchestrated-devices/container-device-interface](https://github.com/container-orchestrated-devices/container-device-interface ), recently podman merged #10081 so it could consume a CDI configuration. 

@elezar I think this would be a good start with podman and GPUs and see how the CDI pipeline would work. I spoke to several vendors to take a look at CDI before implementing their own prestart hook again. 

@mrunalp @bthurber let's take NV (again) as the example for how to enable hardware accelerators in a container "correctly" and get away from using prestart hooks. 

@elezar Can you provide an CDI spec that we could use for testing?
